			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1615">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Thank you for publishing Doug Crandell&rsquo;s essay about his sister who died shortly after birth [&ldquo;<a href="/article/4343">The Sister in Our Dreams</a>,&rdquo; October 2009]. My mother lost a baby girl three years before I was born. It wasn&rsquo;t until I became a mother myself that I understood her loss. But I never really thought about that baby girl being my sister until I read Crandell&rsquo;s account of visiting his own sister&rsquo;s grave. I cried then for the sister I never knew.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Robbie Lewis<br>Camden, Maine</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

